              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "In-memory (JS var)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Low (lost on refresh)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "None"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Acceptable for SPAs with refresh token in cookie"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For web apps, store the access token in memory (a React state or closure) and the refresh token in an "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "HttpOnly; SameSite=Strict",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " cookie. The cookie is sent automatically by the browser but is not accessible to JavaScript."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Set refresh token as HttpOnly cookie on login response\nfrom fastapi.responses import JSONResponse\n\n@router.post(\"/token\")\nasync def login(body: LoginRequest, response: Response):\n    # ... verify credentials ...\n    access_token = create_access_token(user[\"id\"], user[\"scopes\"])\n    refresh_token = create_refresh_token(user[\"id\"])\n\n    response.set_cookie(\n        key=\"refresh_token\",\n        value=refresh_token,\n        httponly=True,\n        secure=True,           # HTTPS only\n        samesite=\"strict\",     # CSRF protection\n        max_age=30 * 24 * 3600,\n    )\n    # Return access token in body (client stores in memory)\n    return {\"access_token\": access_token, \"token_type\": \"bearer\"}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "API Key Rotation (Zero Downtime)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Keys must be rotatable without service interruption. The pattern: issue a new key, allow a grace period where both old and new keys are valid, then revoke the old key:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# app/services/api_keys.py\nimport hashlib, secrets\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom app.services.db import db\n\nasync def rotate_key(user_id: str, old_key_id: str) -> str:\n    # 1. Issue a new key\n    raw = \"sk-\" + secrets.token_urlsafe(32)\n    new_hash = hashlib.sha256(raw.encode()).hexdigest()\n    await db.execute(\n        \"INSERT INTO api_keys (user_id, key_hash, name) VALUES ($1, $2, 'rotated')\",\n        user_id, new_hash,\n    )\n\n    # 2. Schedule old key expiry (grace period: 24h for in-flight requests)\n    await db.execute(\n        \"UPDATE api_keys SET revoked_at = $1 WHERE id = $2 AND user_id = $3\",\n        datetime.now(timezone.utc) + timedelta(hours=24),\n        old_key_id, user_id,\n    )\n\n    # 3. Invalidate cache for old key immediately so new checks hit DB\n    old_row = await db.fetchrow(\"SELECT key_hash FROM api_keys WHERE id = $1\", old_key_id)\n    if old_row:\n        await redis.delete(f\"apikey:{old_row['key_hash']}\")\n\n    return raw  # return new key to caller"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Pitfalls"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Storing raw API keys in the database:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " store only the SHA-256 hash. A database breach should not expose usable keys."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Long-lived JWTs without refresh tokens:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " access tokens should expire in 15 minutes. Use refresh tokens (stored in HttpOnly cookies) to issue new access tokens silently."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Not verifying OIDC id_token signature:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " a provider can return a maliciously crafted token. Always verify the signature against the provider's public keys — use the official library ("
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "google-auth",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ", "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "python-jose",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ")."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Passing provider tokens to downstream services:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " exchange the provider token for your own JWT at the boundary. Internal services should never see or validate third-party tokens."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Missing scope checks:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " authentication (who are you?) and authorization (what can you do?) are separate. A valid token does not mean the caller can access every endpoint."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Choose auth pattern by caller type: API keys for services, JWTs for user sessions, OIDC for social/SSO login. In all cases: hash API keys before storage, keep JWTs short-lived, verify OIDC tokens with the provider's public keys, and enforce scopes at every protected route."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}